          <label>_id</label>
        </input>
      </group>
    </group>
    <group appearance="field-list" ref="/covid_behaviour_change/ebs_intro">
      <label>Learning Objectives</label>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/ebs_intro/intro_note">
        <label>**Community health workers play an important role in recognizing covid-19, educationg others on how to care for a covid patient and reducing stigma. After this module you will:**</label>
      </input>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/ebs_intro/minimize_stigma">
        <label>1. Know how to minimize stigma associated with COVID infection</label>
      </input>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/ebs_intro/patient_assessment">
        <label>2. Know how to assess and risk stratify patients with suspected COVID</label>
      </input>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/ebs_intro/limit_contact">
        <label>3. Know how suspected COVID positive patients can limit contact with others</label>
      </input>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/ebs_intro/reintegration_advice">
        <label>4. Know key messages to advise on reintegration into the household/society</label>
      </input>
    </group>
    <group appearance="field-list" ref="/covid_behaviour_change/stigmatization">
      <label>Stigmatization</label>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/stigmatization/stigma_question">
        <label>**What is stigmatization?**</label>
      </input>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/stigmatization/stigma_definition">
        <label>Stigma occurs when people develop negative associations towards a specific population. As a result, people can be labeled, stereotyped, separated and/or discriminated against.</label>
      </input>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/stigmatization/stigmatization_risks">
        <label>**Risks of stigmatization during the pandemic**</label>
      </input>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/stigmatization/stigma_risks">
        <label>Stigmatization causes more risk when patients:</label>
      </input>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/stigmatization/hide_illness">
        <label>&lt;li style="margin-left:10%;list-style-type:circle"&gt;Hide their illness to avoid being discriminated&lt;/li&gt;</label>
      </input>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/stigmatization/no_help_sought">
        <label>&lt;li style="margin-left:10%;list-style-type:circle"&gt;Don't seek help or healthcare immediately&lt;/li&gt;</label>
      </input>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/stigmatization/unhealthy_behaviours">
        <label>&lt;li style="margin-left:10%;list-style-type:circle"&gt;Don't adopt healthy behaviours&lt;/li&gt;</label>
      </input>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/stigmatization/risk_note">
        <label>Remember that anyone can get COVID. Stigmatizing people can aggravate health problems, increase transmissions and make it more difficult to control the outbreak.</label>
      </input>
    </group>
    <group appearance="field-list" ref="/covid_behaviour_change/assess_patient">
      <label>How to safely and effectively assess a patient</label>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/assess_patient/by_phone">
        <label>It is better to assess and advise a patient by phone, because the virus is easily transmissible.</label>
      </input>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/assess_patient/distance">
        <label>In person, evaluate the patient's symptoms from a distance</label>
      </input>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/assess_patient/ppe">
        <label>Always wear a mask or face covering, and wash your hands afterwards</label>
      </input>
      <input ref="/covid_behaviour_change/assess_patient/patient_assessment_image">
        <label ref="jr:itext('/covid_behaviour_change/assess_patient/patient_assessment_image:label')"/>
      </input>
    </group>
